headline: Organic Carrots Sold at Trader Joe's, Costco Linked to E. Coli Outbreak
summary: The CDC says a new E. coli outbreak has been tied to organic carrots sold at a number of retailers like Trader Joe's and Costco, weeks after an E. coli outbreak took Quarter Pounders off the menu at McDonald's across a dozen states.
